Chase and Current, powered by GE, Collaborate to Cut Energy Use in Branches Across the U.S. | JPMorgan Chase & Co.

























































Skip to main content












×






	Digital Technology Meets The World's Largest LED Installation

	Current, powered by GE and JPMorgan Chase collaborate to reduce environmental impact across 4,500 Chase branches with state-of-the-art sensors, software and controls.

	Here's a breakdown of the impact:


		Current's Digital Technology will reduce Chase's energy consumption by 15%

		Including a 50% reduction in lighting consumption

		That's equivalent to removing 27,000 cars from the road annually for 10 years and

		JPMorgan Chase has committed more than $200 Million to reduce the consumer bank's carbon footprint


	Plus, there's more


		A new app that will reduce water consumption by 20%

		Chase will pilot Current's solar technology at branches across Califorinia


	All helping JPMorgan Chase to:


		Reduce greenhouse gas emissions by 50%

		Offset 100% of employee air travel emissions on an annual basis

		Bring new renewable energy capacity to the grid



	©2017 JPMorgan Chase & Co. all rights reserved.
×



